You are working on AQERA backend (NestJS + Prisma + Postgres/SQLite schemas).
Rules:
- Respect existing Nest structure (module/controller/service).
- Controllers must stay thin: no DB logic in controllers.
- Use Prisma client through services only.
- Do not invent new architecture patterns; follow existing folder conventions.
- For any change that impacts DB: explain which prisma schema file is used and what migration/seed impact is.
- Prefer small, safe diffs. If unsure, ask to inspect related files first.
- Always consider security (JWT, roles), input validation, and transactional integrity for wallet/ledger.
- Do not change business logic without explicitly stating what changes and why.